			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well its been around a month for me as far as playing in the new expansion is concerned and my primary observation is that finding  a group there as a mage is impossible at times or very difficult at best.  I am sure a handful of mages are finding groups there easy to obtain and still others don't care since their guilds are busy with other content.  These are just my findings.
<br />

<br />
I did some thinking and some observation and came up with the following order of group desiribility in GoD:
<br />

<br />
1.  Warrior (Pal can sub if he's well geared), Cleric, and Enchanter.  Without these classes groups in GoD just won't work.  These classes always find work in GoD.
<br />

<br />
2.  Wizard, Rogue, Beastlord (Shaman can sub but it will mean loosing DPS and slow is useful but not really useful on the boss mobs I have seen since they are unslowable). -  You need DPS and you need slow for the trash that can be slowed.  Just makes life easier and these classes give you the most bang for your buck.  These classes find work after 30 min to an hour of LFG on my server.
<br />

<br />
3.  Ranger, Monk, Bard, Druid -  If you want to know whats up in a trial its good to have tracking and its also good to have a puller or some extra healing.  Bards are great to.  Rangers and Monks are important but you can do without them.  These folks usually find a group before mages and necros in GoD though.  These classes fill that last slot well.  Most tend to have an hour long wait max for a group.
<br />

<br />
4.  Everyone else.  Yeah those classes with non-critical functions can basiclly expect a nice long wait or mercy groups.
<br />

<br />

<br />
I have to admit I am very much disgusted with this expansion.  There is no reason why 3 or 4 classes have to be garenteed groups.  This is no way to continue the progression of the EQ universe, at least in PoP and LDON you coudl subsitiute a Druid for a cleric and use a slower in the place of a mezer.  Just seems highly unfair to force group structure though the difficulty of the mobs.
<br />

<br />
I don't even logon anymore unless it is to raid because 4 hours for a group or no possible GoD groups for a mage just plain sucks.
<br />

<br />
Either make it so that we can solo in this brave new world of GoD, give us the ability to convert to another int caster class, or simply expect more mages to quit.  /shrug.<br />_________________<br />Blue Mage</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
