			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Charm has been nerfed. So bard >>> enchanter almost always. Still, you usually need one or the other (although yxxta is an interesting zone, because nothing can be mezzed. I've only done yxxta once though with one group, and we used a bard to pull.)
<br />

<br />
Monks suck. Pathetic dps, bard pulls WAY better, enchanter arguably pulls better.
<br />

<br />
With a little creativity rangers can tank for some of the stuff, if you have two healers and a good slower.
<br />

<br />
Many encounters are different, but if you want a generic-rule-of-thumb I'd say tank (warrior strongly prefered, sk/pal/ranger acceptable but all clearly inferior), cleric, bard/enchanter, back-up-healer(druid, shaman, second cleric), 2 "other" Where other can be really anyone (a backup tank, a high-utility semi-dps (beastlord)). Therefore max number of DPS slots available is 2, and it's really closer to 1-1.5. So mages, necros, wizards, rogues, rangers are all fighting over one spot, when we used to have 2-3 set aside for us in PoP and LDoN.
<br />

<br />
One thing people haven't emphasized here is there still is PoP, especially if you have elemental flags. It's getting easier every day as we get better gear and AA, it's arguably better exp, and it's MUCH more flexible about group makeups. Once you get past the flagging nightmare you could just give up on GoD and go back to PoP and LDoN.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
