				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Either of them > mage in trials.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Eh?  I'm still curious where everyone is getting this misconception that mages simply suck in all aspects.  My guild is one of the elemental-level guilds at best.  We're a family and friends guild that is just now advancing.  In other words, I'm not exactly an uberly equipped magician.  There's a group of friends that always invites me to do GoD trials (sewers, vxed, tipt, but nothing really above those) and other ventures with them--all the members are in one of the top guilds on Solusek Ro.  One of the members in that group is one of the top wizards on Solusek Ro.  His gear is phenomenal (~8.5k buffed hp's) and he's a machine when it comes to damage.  Yet he still insists that my DPS is more reliable and consistent than his, and thus very desireable.  They may have me along for just my companionship and humor, but something tells me they put a lot of stock in my abilities as a mage in general.  Otherwise they could just get a better-equipped guildmate and drag them along to do trials.  
<br />

<br />
In GoD trials with guildies, I feel like I hold down my section of the DPS in the group rather well.  When I'm afk or otherwise preoccupied, the group notices a sharp decline in the rate of dying for mobs and complains about it in /groupsay.  
<br />

<br />
The same goes for hard risk LDoN's, elemental and SRT groups, and any other group I've been involved in.  I've grouped with Time-geared rogues, wizards, etc., and I don't feel like I'm lacking much against them.  They're better geared, thus of course they will be pouring out damage over me.  Yet I'm still invited to their groups, and trusted as a decent enough mage to deal damage alongside them.  
<br />

<br />
What the problem <span style="font-style: italic">probably</span> has been deduced as (though I can't exactly notice this since I'm not advanced far enough) is the fact a time geared mage isn't altogether much more damage than a pre-Time geared mage.  I personally drool over time-focused pets and the ability to actually stand up and take damage when one overaggros due to equipment, but it can't be that bad.  
<br />

<br />
Anyhow, I just refuse to agree that our class is that lacking in the DPS department.  I do agree I wish my pets were sturdier and more of an accentuation of our class skills and source of damage, but I have no problems personally with doing my job as a DD in a group or raid setting.  Maybe I'm living in a shroud of ignorance, but apparently I'm enjoying my class moreso than some others.  Are we really that bad off in the eyes of the majority, though? <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062" taret=_blank>Sage Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a>
<br />
Arch Convoker of Solusek Ro
<br />
<a href="http://www.furiouspantaloons.org"><i>Furious Pantaloons</i></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
