				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Booperbustle wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Either of them > mage in trials.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The same goes for hard risk LDoN's, elemental and SRT groups, and any other group I've been involved in.  I've grouped with Time-geared rogues, wizards, etc., and I don't feel like I'm lacking much against them.  They're better geared, thus of course they will be pouring out damage over me.  Yet I'm still invited to their groups, and trusted as a decent enough mage to deal damage alongside them.  
<br />

<br />
What the problem <span style="font-style: italic">probably</span> has been deduced as (though I can't exactly notice this since I'm not advanced far enough) is the fact a time geared mage isn't altogether much more damage than a pre-Time geared mage.  I personally drool over time-focused pets and the ability to actually stand up and take damage when one overaggros due to equipment, but it can't be that bad.  
<br />

<br />
...<span style="font-weight: bold">Are we really that bad off in the eyes of the majority, though? </span><img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /></td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Bam you hit the nail right on the head!  Right now I'm in an elemental guild that will soon (hopefully <img src="images/smiles/icon_mrgreen.gif" alt="Mr. Green" border="0" />) get into time.  I do damage parses on named mobs in air and earth (just about anything without AE rampage that we can corner-tank) and if I use host and servent I can beat ALL the melees on the raid (unless you count DC pets  <img src="images/smiles/icon_mad.gif" alt="Mad" border="0" />).  The problem is, as soon as we hit time, I'm going to take a back seat.  I've got some old friends in the top guild on RN, and I'd be lucky to pull out half the damage their rogues do right now, and if I get time gear, I'm not going to get much closer to them.  
<br />

<br />
I was in a fire group at C3 2 weeks ago, was necro mage mage wizard druid.  The other mage was fully elemental/time geared with all GoD spells (He had ele/time gear in EVERY slot, including pet focus).  If either of us magicians went afk, the rate mobs were dying didn't change a great deal, it was noticable sure - but it wasn't a big deal.  Then my afformentioned rogue friend showed up and suddenly we were FLYING, you could tell exactly when he walked up and started attacking - and everyone in the group knew it / was commenting about it.  We had cleared EVERY last mob in the castle, and I clocked my AA gain at one every 26 minutes.  He had the Inny dagger and that new stick from GoD with the crazy particle effects, and was otherwise fully time geared.  
<br />

<br />
So to answer your question, in the end game, yes - we are that bad.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370607" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Tiiden Vandorgriffin</a>
